    <h2 {...{
      "id": "aws-access-keys"
    }}>{`AWS Access Keys`}</h2>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "create-access-keys"
    }}>{`Create Access Keys`}</h3>
    <p>{`To enable all `}<strong parentName="p">{`cloud functionalities`}</strong>{`, your need to enter `}<strong parentName="p">{`AWS Access Keys`}</strong>{` that `}<strong parentName="p">{`CloudPanel`}</strong>{` can communicate with `}<strong parentName="p">{`Amazon Web Services`}</strong>{`.`}</p>
    <p>{`To create `}<strong parentName="p">{`AWS Access Keys`}</strong>{` do the following steps:`}</p>
    <p>{`1) Login into the `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://console.aws.amazon.com/ec2/"
      }}>{`AWS Management Console`}</a>{`. `}<br /></p>
    <p>{`2) Click on `}<strong parentName="p">{`Services`}</strong>{` and go to the service `}<strong parentName="p">{`IAM`}</strong>{`.`}</p>
    <p>{`3) In the left menu, click on `}<strong parentName="p">{`Users`}</strong>{` and click on the button `}<strong parentName="p">{`Add user`}</strong>{`.`}</p>
    <p>{`Enter a `}<strong parentName="p">{`User name`}</strong>{` and select `}<strong parentName="p">{`Programmatic access`}</strong>{` as `}<strong parentName="p">{`Access type`}</strong>{` and click on the button `}<strong parentName="p">{`Next: Permissions`}</strong></p>
    <img class="border" src={useBaseUrl('img/v1/cloud_features/aws/add_user_1.png')} /> <br /><br />
    <p>{`4) Click on the button `}<strong parentName="p">{`Attach existing policies directly`}</strong>{` and select the `}<strong parentName="p">{`AdministratorAccess`}</strong>{` policy and click
on the button `}<strong parentName="p">{`Next: Tags`}</strong>{`.`}</p>
    <img class="border" src={useBaseUrl('img/v1/cloud_features/aws/add_user_2.png')} /> <br /><br />
    <div {...{
      "className": "admonition admonition-caution alert alert--warning"
    }}><div parentName="div" {...{
        "className": "admonition-heading"
      }}><h5 parentName="div"><span parentName="h5" {...{
            "className": "admonition-icon"
          }}><svg parentName="span" {...{
              "xmlns": "http://www.w3.org/2000/svg",
              "width": "16",
              "height": "16",
              "viewBox": "0 0 16 16"
            }}><path parentName="svg" {...{
                "fillRule": "evenodd",
                "d": "M8.893 1.5c-.183-.31-.52-.5-.887-.5s-.703.19-.886.5L.138 13.499a.98.98 0 0 0 0 1.001c.193.31.53.501.886.501h13.964c.367 0 .704-.19.877-.5a1.03 1.03 0 0 0 .01-1.002L8.893 1.5zm.133 11.497H6.987v-2.003h2.039v2.003zm0-3.004H6.987V5.987h2.039v4.006z"
              }}></path></svg></span>{`Permissions`}</h5></div><div parentName="div" {...{
        "className": "admonition-content"
      }}><p parentName="div">{`Experienced `}<strong parentName="p">{`AWS`}</strong>{` users should create `}<strong parentName="p">{`AWS Access Keys`}</strong>{` with more fine granulated permissions.`}</p></div></div>
    <p>{`5) Skip the `}<strong parentName="p">{`Add tags (optional)`}</strong>{` step by clicking on the button `}<strong parentName="p">{`Next: Review`}</strong></p>
    <p>{`6) Click on the button `}<strong parentName="p">{`Create user`}</strong>{` to create the `}<strong parentName="p">{`AWS Access Keys`}</strong>{`.`}</p>
    <img class="border" src={useBaseUrl('img/v1/cloud_features/aws/add_user_3.png')} /> <br /><br />
    <p>{`Copy the `}<strong parentName="p">{`Access key ID`}</strong>{` and `}<strong parentName="p">{`Secret access key`}</strong>{`.`}</p>
    <img class="border" src={useBaseUrl('img/v1/cloud_features/aws/add_user_4.png')} />
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "enter-access-keys"
    }}>{`Enter Access Keys`}</h3>
    <p>{`To enter the `}<strong parentName="p">{`AWS Access Keys`}</strong>{` do the following:`}</p>
    <p>{`1) Login into your `}<strong parentName="p">{`CloudPanel`}</strong>{` as `}<strong parentName="p">{`Admin`}</strong>{` and go to the `}<strong parentName="p">{`Admin Adrea`}</strong>{`.`}</p>
    <p>{`2) Click on the left menu on the `}<strong parentName="p">{`AWS`}</strong>{` settings.`}</p>
    <p>{`Enter the `}<strong parentName="p">{`AWS Access Key`}</strong>{` and `}<strong parentName="p">{`AWS Secret Access Key`}</strong>{` and click on the button `}<strong parentName="p">{`Save`}</strong>{`.`}</p>
    <img class="border" src={useBaseUrl('img/v1/cloud_features/aws/enter_access_keys.png')} />
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "instance"
    }}>{`Instance`}</h2>
    <p>{`In this `}<strong parentName="p">{`Instance`}</strong>{` area, you find information about your `}<strong parentName="p">{`Instance`}</strong>{` like `}<strong parentName="p">{`Instance Name`}</strong>{`, `}<strong parentName="p">{`Instance ID`}</strong>{`,
`}<strong parentName="p">{`Instance Type`}</strong>{`, `}<strong parentName="p">{`Region`}</strong>{` and, `}<strong parentName="p">{`IPv4 Public IP`}</strong>{`. `}</p>
    <img class="border" src={useBaseUrl('img/v1/cloud_features/aws/instance.png')} />
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "security-groups"
    }}>{`Security Groups`}</h2>
    <p>{`In this `}<strong parentName="p">{`Security Groups`}</strong>{` area, you see all assigned `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSEC2/latest/UserGuide/ec2-security-groups.html"
      }}>{`Security Groups`}</a>{` of your `}<strong parentName="p">{`Instance`}</strong>{`.`}<br />{`
With a click on a `}<strong parentName="p">{`Security Group`}</strong>{`, you can edit rules like adding IPs for SSH or other services.`}</p>
    <img class="border" src={useBaseUrl('img/v1/cloud_features/aws/security_groups.png')} />
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "adding-a-rule"
    }}>{`Adding a Rule`}</h3>
    <p>{`To `}<strong parentName="p">{`Add a Rule`}</strong>{` click on the `}<strong parentName="p">{`Security Group`}</strong>{` and then on the button `}<strong parentName="p">{`Add Rule`}</strong>{` top right.`}</p>
    <img class="border" src={useBaseUrl('img/v1/cloud_features/aws/add_security_group_rules.png')} /> <br /><br />
    <p>{`Select a `}<strong parentName="p">{`Rule Type`}</strong>{` from a list and select the `}<strong parentName="p">{`Source`}</strong>{`, which should have access to the service.`}</p>
    <img class="border" src={useBaseUrl('img/v1/cloud_features/aws/add_security_group_rule.png')} />
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "deleting-a-rule"
    }}>{`Deleting a Rule`}</h3>
    <p>{`On the `}<strong parentName="p">{`Security Group`}</strong>{` overview site you can delete a rule by clicking on the button `}<strong parentName="p">{`Delete`}</strong>{`.`}</p>
    <img class="border" src={useBaseUrl('img/v1/cloud_features/aws/add_security_group_rules.png')} /> 
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "route-53"
    }}>{`Route 53`}</h2>
    <p><a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://aws.amazon.com/route53/"
      }}>{`Amazon Route 53`}</a>{` is a highly available and scalable cloud Domain Name System (DNS) web service. `}<br />{`
It is designed to give developers and businesses a reliable and cost-effective way to route end users to Internet applications
by translating names like `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "http://www.example.com"
      }}>{`www.example.com`}</a>{` into the numeric IP addresses like 8.8.8.8 that computers use to connect to each other.`}</p>
    <p>{`In this `}<strong parentName="p">{`Route 53`}</strong>{` area, you can import `}<strong parentName="p">{`Hosted Zones`}</strong>{` from `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://aws.amazon.com/route53/"
      }}>{`Amazon Route 53`}</a>{` or create new zones to manage.`}</p>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "new-hosted-zone"
    }}>{`New Hosted Zone`}</h3>
    <p>{`To create a `}<strong parentName="p">{`New Hosted Zone`}</strong>{`, click on the button top right on `}<strong parentName="p">{`New Hosted Zone`}</strong>{`.`}</p>
    <img class="border" src={useBaseUrl('img/v1/cloud_features/aws/new_route53_hosted_zone.png')} /> <br /> <br />
    <p>{`Enter the `}<strong parentName="p">{`Domain Name`}</strong>{` and click on `}<strong parentName="p">{`Add Hosted Zone`}</strong>{` to create a new `}<strong parentName="p">{`Hosted Zone`}</strong>{` in `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://aws.amazon.com/route53/"
      }}>{`Amazon Route 53`}</a>{`.`}</p>
    <img class="border" src={useBaseUrl('img/v1/cloud_features/aws/new_route53_hosted_zone_domain.png')} />
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "import-hosted-zone"
    }}>{`Import Hosted Zone`}</h3>
    <p>{`If you already have an existing `}<strong parentName="p">{`Hosted Zone`}</strong>{` in your `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://aws.amazon.com/route53/"
      }}>{`Amazon Route 53`}</a>{`, and if you want to manage the DNS records via
`}<strong parentName="p">{`CloudPanel`}</strong>{`, you can import the `}<strong parentName="p">{`Hosted Zone`}</strong>{`.`}</p>
    <p>{`To import an existing `}<strong parentName="p">{`Hosted Zone`}</strong>{`, click on the button top right on `}<strong parentName="p">{`Import Hosted Zone`}</strong>{`.`}</p>
    <img class="border" src={useBaseUrl('img/v1/cloud_features/aws/import_hosted_zone.png')} /> <br /> <br />
    <p>{`The `}<strong parentName="p">{`Hosted Zone ID`}</strong>{` of a `}<strong parentName="p">{`Domain Name`}</strong>{` can be found in the `}<strong parentName="p">{`AWS Management Console`}</strong>{` -> `}<strong parentName="p">{`Services`}</strong>{` -> `}<strong parentName="p">{`Route 53`}</strong>{`.`}</p>
    <img class="border" src={useBaseUrl('img/v1/cloud_features/aws/aws_route53_hosted_zone_id.png')} />
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "adding-a-dns-record"
    }}>{`Adding a DNS Record`}</h3>
    <p>{`To add a `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://docs.aws.amazon.com/Route53/latest/DeveloperGuide/ResourceRecordTypes.html"
      }}>{`DNS Record`}</a>{`, click on your `}<strong parentName="p">{`Hosted Zone`}</strong>{` and click on the button `}<strong parentName="p">{`Add Record`}</strong>{` top right.`}</p>
    <img class="border" src={useBaseUrl('img/v1/cloud_features/aws/add_dns_record_hosted_zone.png')} /> <br /> <br />
    <p>{`Select the `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://docs.aws.amazon.com/Route53/latest/DeveloperGuide/ResourceRecordTypes.html"
      }}>{`Type`}</a>{`, enter the `}<strong parentName="p">{`Name`}</strong>{`, `}<strong parentName="p">{`Value`}</strong>{`,
and select the `}<strong parentName="p">{`TTL`}</strong>{` before clicking on the button `}<strong parentName="p">{`Add Record`}</strong>{`.`}</p>
    <img class="border" src={useBaseUrl('img/v1/cloud_features/aws/add_dns_record.png')} />
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "deleting-a-dns-record"
    }}>{`Deleting a DNS Record`}</h3>
    <p>{`To delete a `}<strong parentName="p">{`DNS Record`}</strong>{`, click on your `}<strong parentName="p">{`Hosted Zone`}</strong>{` and click on the button `}<strong parentName="p">{`Delete`}</strong>{`.`}</p>
    <img class="border" src={useBaseUrl('img/v1/cloud_features/aws/delete_dns_record.png')} />
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "amazon-machine-images-ami"
    }}>{`Amazon Machine Images (AMI)`}</h2>
    <p>{`An `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSEC2/latest/UserGuide/AMIs.html"
      }}>{`Amazon Machine Image (AMI)`}</a>{` is a special type of virtual appliance that is
used to create a virtual machine within the `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://aws.amazon.com/ec2/"
      }}>{`Amazon Elastic Compute Cloud (EC2)`}</a>{`.`}</p>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "automatic-backups"
    }}>{`Automatic Backups`}</h3>
    <p>{`We use `}<strong parentName="p">{`AMIs`}</strong>{` to backup the entire `}<strong parentName="p">{`Instance`}</strong>{`, including all disks. All `}<strong parentName="p">{`AMIs`}</strong>{` are done incrementally, which means the first image
is a full backup, and all further `}<strong parentName="p">{`AMIs`}</strong>{` contain the data differences.`}</p>
    <p>{`To enable `}<strong parentName="p">{`Automatic Backups`}</strong>{` do the following:`}</p>
    <p>{`1) Login into your `}<strong parentName="p">{`CloudPanel`}</strong>{` as `}<strong parentName="p">{`Admin`}</strong>{` and go to the `}<strong parentName="p">{`Admin Adrea`}</strong>{`.`}</p>
    <p>{`2) Click on the left menu on the `}<strong parentName="p">{`AWS`}</strong>{` settings.`}</p>
    <p>{`Set `}<strong parentName="p">{`Automatic Backups`}</strong>{` to `}<strong parentName="p">{`Yes`}</strong>{` and select the `}<strong parentName="p">{`Backup Frequency`}</strong>{` and `}<strong parentName="p">{`Backup Retention Period`}</strong>{`.`}</p>
    <img class="border" src={useBaseUrl('img/v1/cloud_features/aws/enable_automatic_backups.png')} /> <br /><br />
    <p>{`With the following configuration, two `}<strong parentName="p">{`Backups (AMIs)`}</strong>{` will be created per day and held for seven days, 14 `}<strong parentName="p">{`AMIs`}</strong>{` in total.`}</p>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "manual-backups"
    }}>{`Manual Backups`}</h3>
    <p>{`Often you want to do a backup before releasing a new version of your application, and you want to retain the manually created backup
for some time.`}</p>
    <p>{`To create a `}<strong parentName="p">{`Backup`}</strong>{`, click on the tab `}<strong parentName="p">{`Backup (AMIs)`}</strong>{` and then on the button `}<strong parentName="p">{`Create Backup`}</strong>{` top right.`}</p>
    <img class="border" src={useBaseUrl('img/v1/cloud_features/aws/create_manual_backup_1.png')} /> <br /><br />
    <p>{`Enter the `}<strong parentName="p">{`Name`}</strong>{` of your `}<strong parentName="p">{`Backup (AMI)`}</strong>{` and click on the button `}<strong parentName="p">{`Create Backup`}</strong>{`.  `}<br />{`
AWS will immediately start creating an `}<strong parentName="p">{`AMI`}</strong>{` of your `}<strong parentName="p">{`Instance`}</strong>{`.`}</p>
    <img class="border" src={useBaseUrl('img/v1/cloud_features/aws/create_manual_backup_2.png')} /> <br /><br />
    <div {...{
      "className": "admonition admonition-important alert alert--info"
    }}><div parentName="div" {...{
